Source: mini-sendmail
Section: mail
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Stefan Schlesinger <sts@ono.at>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.50~)
Standards-Version: 3.9.4
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/sts/mini_sendmail
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/sts/mini_sendmail.git -b master

Package: mini-sendmail
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Homepage: https://wiki.mattrude.com/Mini_sendmail
Description: Reads its standard input up to an end-of-file and sends a copy of the
 message found there to all of the addresses listed. The message is sent
 by connecting to a local SMTP server. This means mini_sendmail can be
 used to send email from inside a chroot(2) area.

